<h2>Tutorial - Page 1</h2>
<p>Coding a website is an exciting journey into the world of web development. 
    <br> Whether you're a beginner or an experienced coder, building a website involves several key steps. 
    <br> First, you'll need to plan your website's structure and design, considering factors such as the target audience, purpose, and content. 
    <br> Next, you'll choose the appropriate technologies and tools for your project, such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. 
    <br> HTML provides the structure of your website, CSS adds styling and layout, and JavaScript adds interactivity and dynamic features. 
    <br> As you start coding, it's important to organize your files and directories efficiently, keeping your code clean and maintainable. 
    <br> Throughout the process, testing and debugging your code regularly will help ensure a smooth user experience. 
    <br> Once your website is complete, you'll need to deploy it to a web server so that it's accessible to users worldwide. 
    <br> Whether you're building a personal blog, an e-commerce site, or a portfolio, coding a website is a rewarding endeavor that allows you to showcase your creativity and technical skills.</p>
